According to Law on Cybersecurity and Personal Data Protection, the processing of personal data is confidential, it must be carried out exclusively by persons acting under the authority of the Data controller, and only on his instructions.&nbsp;
The Data controller is required to take all necessary precautions, in view of the nature of the data, and in particular to prevent it from being distorted, damaged or accessed by unauthorised third parties.&nbsp;Last modified 20 Dec 2021
				
			